[[Image:Walpi arizona.jpg|thumb|right|Walpi, circa 1920]]
'''Walpi''' is a [[village]] in [[Navajo County]], [[Arizona]], north east of [[Flagstaff, Arizona|Flagstaff]]. It is on [[First Mesa, Arizona|First Mesa]] in the [[Hopi Reservation]]. It is inhabited mainly by the [[Hopi]]-speaking [[Pueblo people|Pueblo]] ([[Tewa]]), several of whom (about half a dozen in number) live without running water or electricity. Walpi one of the oldest continuously inhabited village in the United States. {{Citation needed|date=May 2009}} <!-- Old Oraibi and Acoma usually get that title. Taos also claims to be oldest -->

